title: Simplified Lot Quality Assurance Sampling Evaluation of Access and Coverage (SLEAC) Tools
text: useful able assess performance classifier chosen SLEAC survey. example, context presented area population 600, sample size 40 60% 90% threshold classifier, performance classifier can assessed first simulating population determining classification probabilities chosen classifier population. diagnostic test can also plotted.
code: ## Simulate population ---- lqas_sim_pop <- lqas_simulate_test(   pop = 600, n = 40, dLower = 0.6, dUpper = 0.9 )  ## Get classification probabilities ---- lqas_get_class_prob(lqas_sim_pop) #>                     Low : 0.9552 #>                Moderate : 0.8305 #>                    High : 0.8395 #>                 Overall : 0.9062 #> Gross misclassification : 0 plot(lqas_sim_pop)

title: Simplified Lot Quality Assurance Sampling Evaluation of Access and Coverage (SLEAC) Tools
text: SLEAC implemented several service delivery units, also possible estimate overall coverage across service delivery units. example, using survey_data dataset national SLEAC survey conducted Sierra Leone, overall coverage estimate can calculated. , additional information total population service delivery unit surveyed needed. Sierra Leone example, pop_data dataset gives population district Sierra Leone. overall coverage estimate can calculated follows: gives following results:
code: pop_data #> # A tibble: 14 × 2 #>    district               pop #>    <chr>                <dbl> #>  1 Kailahun            526379 #>  2 Kenema              609891 #>  3 Kono                506100 #>  4 Bombali             606544 #>  5 Kambia              345474 #>  6 Koinadugu           409372 #>  7 Port Loko           615376 #>  8 Tonkolili           531435 #>  9 Bo                  575478 #> 10 Bonthe              200781 #> 11 Moyamba             318588 #> 12 Pujehun             346461 #> 13 Western Area Rural  444270 #> 14 Western Area Urban 1055964 pop_df <- pop_data |>   setNames(nm = c("strata", "pop"))  estimate_coverage_overall(   survey_data, pop_data, strata = "district", u5 = 0.177, p = 0.01 ) #> $cf #> $cf$estimate #> [1] 0.1257481 #>  #> $cf$ci #> [1] 0.09247579 0.15902045 #>  #>  #> $tc #> $tc$estimate #> [1] 0.1706466 #>  #> $tc$ci #> [1] 0.1371647 0.2041284

title: Simplified Lot Quality Assurance Sampling Evaluation of Access and Coverage (SLEAC) Tools — sleacr
text: recent past, measurement coverage mainly two-stage cluster sampled surveys either part nutrition assessment specific coverage survey known Centric Systematic Area Sampling (CSAS). However, methods resource intensive often used final programme evaluation meaning results arrive late programme adaptation. SLEAC, stands Simplified Lot Quality Assurance Sampling Evaluation Access Coverage, low resource method designed specifically address limitation used regularly monitoring, planning importantly, timely improvement programme quality, agency Ministry Health (MoH) led programmes. package provides functions use conducting SLEAC assessment.
